{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":485,"text":"Ten years ago, I wrote a book which I entitled"},{"time":2707,"text":"\"Our Final Century?\" Question mark."},{"time":5800,"text":"My publishers cut out the question mark. (Laughter)"},{"time":9377,"text":"The American publishers changed our title"},{"time":11259,"text":"to \"Our Final Hour.\""},{"time":15168,"text":"Americans like instant gratification and the reverse."},{"time":18660,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":20368,"text":"And my theme was this:"},{"time":22118,"text":"Our Earth has existed for 45 million centuries,"},{"time":26284,"text":"but this one is special —"},{"time":28297,"text":"it's the first where one species, ours,"},{"time":31313,"text":"has the planet's future in its hands."},{"time":34115,"text":"Over nearly all of Earth's history,"},{"time":36105,"text":"threats have come from nature —"},{"time":38041,"text":"disease, earthquakes, asteroids and so forth —"},{"time":41537,"text":"but from now on, the worst dangers come from us."},{"time":47209,"text":"And it's now not just the nuclear threat;"},{"time":50480,"text":"in our interconnected world,"},{"time":52231,"text":"network breakdowns can cascade globally;"},{"time":55394,"text":"air travel can spread pandemics\nworldwide within days;"},{"time":59350,"text":"and social media can spread panic and rumor"},{"time":62677,"text":"literally at the speed of light."},{"time":65894,"text":"We fret too much about minor hazards —"},{"time":69119,"text":"improbable air crashes, carcinogens in food,"},{"time":73150,"text":"low radiation doses, and so forth —"},{"time":75376,"text":"but we and our political masters"},{"time":78201,"text":"are in denial about catastrophic scenarios."},{"time":82404,"text":"The worst have thankfully not yet happened."},{"time":85442,"text":"Indeed, they probably won't."},{"time":87638,"text":"But if an event is potentially devastating,"},{"time":90823,"text":"it's worth paying a substantial premium"},{"time":93691,"text":"to safeguard against it, even if it's unlikely,"},{"time":97527,"text":"just as we take out fire insurance on our house."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102040,"text":"And as science offers greater power and promise,"},{"time":107037,"text":"the downside gets scarier too."},{"time":110903,"text":"We get ever more vulnerable."},{"time":113142,"text":"Within a few decades,"},{"time":114980,"text":"millions will have the capability"},{"time":117210,"text":"to misuse rapidly advancing biotech,"},{"time":120331,"text":"just as they misuse cybertech today."},{"time":123884,"text":"Freeman Dyson, in a TED Talk,"},{"time":127083,"text":"foresaw that children will design\nand create new organisms"},{"time":130679,"text":"just as routinely as his generation\nplayed with chemistry sets."},{"time":135190,"text":"Well, this may be on the science fiction fringe,"},{"time":137718,"text":"but were even part of his scenario to come about,"},{"time":140901,"text":"our ecology and even our species"},{"time":143638,"text":"would surely not survive long unscathed."},{"time":147627,"text":"For instance, there are some eco-extremists"},{"time":151490,"text":"who think that it would be better for the planet,"},{"time":153999,"text":"for Gaia, if there were far fewer humans."},{"time":157402,"text":"What happens when such people have mastered"},{"time":160119,"text":"synthetic biology techniques"},{"time":162256,"text":"that will be widespread by 2050?"},{"time":165108,"text":"And by then, other science fiction nightmares"},{"time":168150,"text":"may transition to reality:"},{"time":169860,"text":"dumb robots going rogue,"},{"time":171930,"text":"or a network that develops a mind of its own"},{"time":174347,"text":"threatens us all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176936,"text":"Well, can we guard against such risks by regulation?"},{"time":180206,"text":"We must surely try, but these enterprises"},{"time":182613,"text":"are so competitive, so globalized,"},{"time":186142,"text":"and so driven by commercial pressure,"},{"time":188122,"text":"that anything that can be done\nwill be done somewhere,"},{"time":191407,"text":"whatever the regulations say."},{"time":193443,"text":"It's like the drug laws — we try to regulate, but can't."},{"time":196930,"text":"And the global village will have its village idiots,"},{"time":199974,"text":"and they'll have a global range."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203470,"text":"So as I said in my book,"},{"time":205761,"text":"we'll have a bumpy ride through this century."},{"time":208650,"text":"There may be setbacks to our society —"},{"time":212140,"text":"indeed, a 50 percent chance of a severe setback."},{"time":216255,"text":"But are there conceivable events"},{"time":219169,"text":"that could be even worse,"},{"time":221330,"text":"events that could snuff out all life?"},{"time":224760,"text":"When a new particle accelerator came online,"},{"time":227686,"text":"some people anxiously asked,"},{"time":229475,"text":"could it destroy the Earth or, even worse,"},{"time":231725,"text":"rip apart the fabric of space?"},{"time":234384,"text":"Well luckily, reassurance could be offered."},{"time":237927,"text":"I and others pointed out that nature"},{"time":239971,"text":"has done the same experiments"},{"time":241904,"text":"zillions of times already,"},{"time":244090,"text":"via cosmic ray collisions."},{"time":245855,"text":"But scientists should surely be precautionary"},{"time":248909,"text":"about experiments that generate conditions"},{"time":251489,"text":"without precedent in the natural world."},{"time":253972,"text":"Biologists should avoid release\nof potentially devastating"},{"time":257395,"text":"genetically modified pathogens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260110,"text":"And by the way, our special aversion"},{"time":263627,"text":"to the risk of truly existential disasters"},{"time":267088,"text":"depends on a philosophical and ethical question,"},{"time":270363,"text":"and it's this:"},{"time":272033,"text":"Consider two scenarios."},{"time":274341,"text":"Scenario A wipes out 90 percent of humanity."},{"time":279577,"text":"Scenario B wipes out 100 percent."},{"time":283473,"text":"How much worse is B than A?"},{"time":286391,"text":"Some would say 10 percent worse."},{"time":289414,"text":"The body count is 10 percent higher."},{"time":292564,"text":"But I claim that B is incomparably worse."},{"time":295470,"text":"As an astronomer, I can't believe"},{"time":298099,"text":"that humans are the end of the story."},{"time":300566,"text":"It is five billion years before the sun flares up,"},{"time":303889,"text":"and the universe may go on forever,"},{"time":306600,"text":"so post-human evolution,"},{"time":308892,"text":"here on Earth and far beyond,"},{"time":311082,"text":"could be as prolonged as the Darwinian process"},{"time":313796,"text":"that's led to us, and even more wonderful."},{"time":317077,"text":"And indeed, future evolution\nwill happen much faster,"},{"time":319741,"text":"on a technological timescale,"},{"time":321940,"text":"not a natural selection timescale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":324239,"text":"So we surely, in view of those immense stakes,"},{"time":328434,"text":"shouldn't accept even a one in a billion risk"},{"time":331820,"text":"that human extinction would foreclose"},{"time":334049,"text":"this immense potential."},{"time":336359,"text":"Some scenarios that have been envisaged"},{"time":338131,"text":"may indeed be science fiction,"},{"time":339950,"text":"but others may be disquietingly real."},{"time":343336,"text":"It's an important maxim that the unfamiliar"},{"time":346210,"text":"is not the same as the improbable,"},{"time":348907,"text":"and in fact, that's why we at Cambridge University"},{"time":351305,"text":"are setting up a center to study how to mitigate"},{"time":354680,"text":"these existential risks."},{"time":356712,"text":"It seems it's worthwhile just for a few people"},{"time":359775,"text":"to think about these potential disasters."},{"time":362091,"text":"And we need all the help we can get from others,"},{"time":365104,"text":"because we are stewards of a precious"},{"time":367583,"text":"pale blue dot in a vast cosmos,"},{"time":371066,"text":"a planet with 50 million centuries ahead of it."},{"time":374444,"text":"And so let's not jeopardize that future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":377000,"text":"And I'd like to finish with a quote"},{"time":378795,"text":"from a great scientist called Peter Medawar."},{"time":382296,"text":"I quote, \"The bells that toll for mankind"},{"time":385569,"text":"are like the bells of Alpine cattle."},{"time":388213,"text":"They are attached to our own necks,"},{"time":390499,"text":"and it must be our fault if they do not make"},{"time":393174,"text":"a tuneful and melodious sound.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":395305,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397572,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}